33// Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
34// BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35// the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
36// static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
37// BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
38#ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
39# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
40#elif USING_V8_SHARED
41# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
42#else
43# define V8_EXPORT
44#endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
45
46#else // V8_OS_WIN
47
48// Setup for Linux shared library export.
49#if V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_VISIBILITY
50# ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
51# define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
52# else
53# define V8_EXPORT
54# endif
55#else
56# define V8_EXPORT
57#endif
58
59#endif // V8_OS_WIN

156#define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
157 while (false) { \
158 *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
159 }
160
192template <class T>
193class Local {
194 public:
195 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
196 template <class S>
197 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
198 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
204 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
205 }
206
210 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
211
215 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
216
217 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
218
219 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
220
227 template <class S>
228 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
229 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
230 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
231 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
232 if (b == 0) return false;
233 return *a == *b;
234 }
235
236 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
237 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
238 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
239 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
240 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
241 if (b == 0) return false;
242 return *a == *b;
243 }
244
251 template <class S>
252 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
253 return !operator==(that);
254 }
255
256 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
257 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
258 return !operator==(that);
259 }
260
266 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
267#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
268 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
269 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
270 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
271#endif
272 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
273 }
274
280 template <class S>
281 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
282 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
283 }
284
290 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
291 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
292 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
293
294 private:
295 friend class Utils;
296 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
297 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
298 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
299 template<class F> friend class Local;
300 template <class F>
301 friend class MaybeLocal;
302 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
303 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
304 friend class String;
305 friend class Object;
306 friend class Context;
307 friend class Private;
308 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
309 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
310 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
311 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
312 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
313 friend class HandleScope;
314 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
315 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
316 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
317 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
318 template <class F>
319 friend class ReturnValue;
320
321 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
322 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
323 T* val_;
324};

344template <class T>
345class MaybeLocal {
346 public:
347 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
348 template <class S>
349 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
350 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
351 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
352 }
353
354 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
355
360 template <class S>
361 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
362 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
363 return !IsEmpty();
364 }
365
370 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
371
376 template <class S>
377 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
378 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
379 }
380
381 private:
382 T* val_;
383};

392 template <class S>

395 }
396 // Can only be safely called if already set.

398 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
399 template<class S> V8_INLINE void Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle);
400
401 private:
402 T* val_;
403};

406static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
407static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
408
409template <typename T>
410class WeakCallbackInfo {
411 public:
412 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
413
414 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
415 void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
416 Callback* callback)
417 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
418 for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
419 embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
420 }
421 }
422
423 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
424 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
425 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
426
427 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
428 void* GetInternalField1() const) {
429 return embedder_fields_[0];
430 }
431 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
432 void* GetInternalField2() const) {
433 return embedder_fields_[1];
434 }
435
436 V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
437 bool IsFirstPass() const) {
438 return callback_ != nullptr;
439 }
440
441 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
442 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
443 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
444 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
445 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
446 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
447 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
448
449 private:
450 Isolate* isolate_;
451 T* parameter_;
452 Callback* callback_;
453 void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
454};
455
456
457// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
458// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
459// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
460// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
461// possible to request a second pass callback.
462enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
463
477template <class T> class PersistentBase {
478 public:
483 V8_INLINE void Reset();
488 template <class S>
489 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
490
495 template <class S>
496 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& other);
497
498 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == NULL; }
499 V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
500
501 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
502 return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
503 }
504
505 template <class S>
506 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
507 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
508 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
509 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
510 if (b == NULL) return false;
511 return *a == *b;
512 }
513
514 template <class S>
515 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
516 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
517 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
518 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
519 if (b == NULL) return false;
520 return *a == *b;
521 }
522
523 template <class S>
524 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
525 return !operator==(that);
526 }
527
528 template <class S>
529 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
530 return !operator==(that);
531 }
532
540 template <typename P>
541 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
542 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
543 WeakCallbackType type);
544
552 V8_INLINE void SetWeak();
553
554 template<typename P>
555 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
556
557 // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
558 V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }
559
565 V8_INLINE void RegisterExternalReference(Isolate* isolate) const;
566
573 V8_INLINE void MarkIndependent();
574
580 V8_INLINE void MarkActive();
581
582 V8_INLINE bool IsIndependent() const;
583
585 V8_INLINE bool IsNearDeath() const;
586
588 V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
589
594 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
595
600 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
601
602 PersistentBase(const PersistentBase& other) = delete; // NOLINT
603 void operator=(const PersistentBase&) = delete;
604
605 private:
606 friend class Isolate;
607 friend class Utils;
608 template<class F> friend class Local;
609 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
610 template <class F>
611 friend class Global;
612 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
613 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
614 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
615 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
616 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
617 friend class Object;
618
619 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
620 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
621
622 T* val_;
623};

673template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
674 public:
678 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
684 template <class S>
685 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
686 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
687 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
688 }
694 template <class S, class M2>
695 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
696 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
697 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
698 }
705 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
706 Copy(that);
707 }
708 template <class S, class M2>
709 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
710 Copy(that);
711 }
712 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
713 Copy(that);
714 return *this;
715 }
716 template <class S, class M2>
717 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
718 Copy(that);
719 return *this;
720 }
726 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
727 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
728 }
729
730 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
731 template <class S>
732 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
733#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
734 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
735 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
736 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
737#endif
738 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
739 }
740
741 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
742 template <class S>
743 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
744 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
745 }
746
747 private:
748 friend class Isolate;
749 friend class Utils;
750 template<class F> friend class Local;
751 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
752 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
753
754 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
755 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
756 template<class S, class M2>
757 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
758};

766template <class T>
767class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
768 public:
772 V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
778 template <class S>
779 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
780 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
781 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
782 }
788 template <class S>
789 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
790 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
791 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
792 }
796 V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
797 other.val_ = nullptr;
798 }
799 V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
803 template <class S>
804 V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
805 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
806 if (this != &rhs) {
807 this->Reset();
808 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
809 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
810 }
811 return *this;
812 }
816 Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
817
818 /*
819 * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
820 */
821 typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
822
823 Global(const Global&) = delete;
824 void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
825
826 private:
827 template <class F>
828 friend class ReturnValue;
829 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
830};

966class ScriptOriginOptions {
967 public:
968 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
969 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
970 bool is_module = false)
971 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
972 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
973 (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
974 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
975 : flags_(flags &
976 (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
977
978 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
979 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
980 }
981 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
982 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
983 bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
984
985 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
986
987 private:
988 enum {
989 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
990 kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
991 kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
992 kIsModule = 1 << 3
993 };
994 const int flags_;
995};

1036class V8_EXPORT UnboundScript {

1169class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1170 public:
1178 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1179 enum BufferPolicy {
1180 BufferNotOwned,
1181 BufferOwned
1182 };
1183
1184 CachedData()
1185 : data(NULL),
1186 length(0),
1187 rejected(false),
1188 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1189
1190 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1191 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1192 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1193 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1194 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1195 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1196 ~CachedData();
1197 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1198 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1199 const uint8_t* data;
1200 int length;
1201 bool rejected;
1202 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1203
1204 // Prevent copying.
1205 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1206 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1207 };
1208
1212 class Source {
1213 public:
1214 // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1215 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1216 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1217 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1218 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1219 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1220
1221 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1222 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1223 // alive.
1224 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1225
1226 V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1227
1228 // Prevent copying.
1229 Source(const Source&) = delete;
1230 Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1231
1232 private:
1233 friend class ScriptCompiler;
1234
1235 Local<String> source_string;
1236
1237 // Origin information
1238 Local<Value> resource_name;
1239 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1240 Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1241 ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1242 Local<Value> source_map_url;
1243
1244 // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1245 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1246 // set when calling a compile method.
1247 CachedData* cached_data;
1248 };

2395class V8_EXPORT String : public Name {
2396 public:
2397 static const int kMaxLength = (1 << 28) - 16;
2398
2399 enum Encoding {
2400 UNKNOWN_ENCODING = 0x1,
2401 TWO_BYTE_ENCODING = 0x0,
2402 ONE_BYTE_ENCODING = 0x8
2403 };
2407 int Length() const;
2408
2413 int Utf8Length() const;
2414
2421 bool IsOneByte() const;
2422
2428 bool ContainsOnlyOneByte() const;
2429
2455 enum WriteOptions {
2456 NO_OPTIONS = 0,
2457 HINT_MANY_WRITES_EXPECTED = 1,
2458 NO_NULL_TERMINATION = 2,
2459 PRESERVE_ONE_BYTE_NULL = 4,
2460 // Used by WriteUtf8 to replace orphan surrogate code units with the
2461 // unicode replacement character. Needs to be set to guarantee valid UTF-8
2462 // output.
2463 REPLACE_INVALID_UTF8 = 8
2464 };

2998 // Implements CreateDataProperty (ECMA-262, 7.3.4).
2999 //
3000 // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value
3001 // on the object unless the property already exists and is not configurable
3002 // or the object is not extensible.
3003 //
3004 // Returns true on success.

3015 // for specifying attributes.
3016 //
3017 // Returns true on success.

3019 Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, Local<Value> value,
3020 PropertyAttribute attributes = None);
3021
3022 // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3023 //
3024 // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3025 // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3026 //
3027 // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3028 //
3029 // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3030 // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3031 //
3032 // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
3033 //
3034 // Returns true on success.
3035 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineProperty(
3036 Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, PropertyDescriptor& descriptor);
3037
3038 // Sets an own property on this object bypassing interceptors and
3039 // overriding accessors or read-only properties.
3040 //
3041 // Note that if the object has an interceptor the property will be set
3042 // locally, but since the interceptor takes precedence the local property
3043 // will only be returned if the interceptor doesn't return a value.
3044 //
3045 // Note also that this only works for named properties.
3046 V8_DEPRECATED("Use CreateDataProperty / DefineOwnProperty",
3047 bool ForceSet(Local<Value> key, Local<Value> value,
3048 PropertyAttribute attribs = None));
3049 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use CreateDataProperty / DefineOwnProperty",
3050 Maybe<bool> ForceSet(Local<Context> context,
3051 Local<Value> key, Local<Value> value,
3052 PropertyAttribute attribs = None));

3525 public:
3526 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3527 : value_(that.value_) {
3528 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3529 }
3530 // Local setters
3531 template <typename S>
3532 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Global<> instead",
3533 void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3534 template <typename S>
3535 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3536 template <typename S>
3537 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3538 // Fast primitive setters
3539 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3540 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3541 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3542 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3543 // Fast JS primitive setters
3544 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3545 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3546 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3547 // Convenience getter for Isolate
3548 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
3549
3550 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3551 template <typename S>
3552 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3553
3554 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3555 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3556 // value.
3557 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3558
3559 private:
3560 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3561 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
3562 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
3563 template <class F, class G, class H>
3564 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
3565 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Object* value) { *value_ = value; }
3566 V8_INLINE internal::Object* GetDefaultValue();
3567 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Object** slot);
3568 internal::Object** value_;
3569};

4016// TODO(mtrofin): rename WasmCompiledModule to WasmModuleObject, for
4017// consistency with internal APIs.
4018class V8_EXPORT WasmCompiledModule : public Object {
4019 public:
4020 typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> SerializedModule;
4021 // A buffer that is owned by the caller.
4022 typedef std::pair<const uint8_t*, size_t> CallerOwnedBuffer;
4023
4024 // An opaque, native heap object for transferring wasm modules. It
4025 // supports move semantics, and does not support copy semantics.
4026 class TransferrableModule final {
4027 public:
4028 TransferrableModule(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4029 TransferrableModule(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4030
4031 TransferrableModule& operator=(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4032 TransferrableModule& operator=(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4033
4034 private:
4035 typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> OwnedBuffer;
4036 friend class WasmCompiledModule;
4037 TransferrableModule(OwnedBuffer&& code, OwnedBuffer&& bytes)
4038 : compiled_code(std::move(code)), wire_bytes(std::move(bytes)) {}
4039
4040 OwnedBuffer compiled_code = {nullptr, 0};
4041 OwnedBuffer wire_bytes = {nullptr, 0};
4042 };
4043
4044 // Get an in-memory, non-persistable, and context-independent (meaning,
4045 // suitable for transfer to another Isolate and Context) representation
4046 // of this wasm compiled module.
4047 TransferrableModule GetTransferrableModule();
4048
4049 // Efficiently re-create a WasmCompiledModule, without recompiling, from
4050 // a TransferrableModule.
4051 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> FromTransferrableModule(
4052 Isolate* isolate, const TransferrableModule&);
4053
4054 // Get the wasm-encoded bytes that were used to compile this module.
4055 Local<String> GetWasmWireBytes();
4056
4057 // Serialize the compiled module. The serialized data does not include the
4058 // uncompiled bytes.
4059 SerializedModule Serialize();
4060
4061 // If possible, deserialize the module, otherwise compile it from the provided
4062 // uncompiled bytes.
4063 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> DeserializeOrCompile(
4064 Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4065 const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4066 V8_INLINE static WasmCompiledModule* Cast(Value* obj);
4067
4068 private:
4069 // TODO(ahaas): please remove the friend once streamed compilation is
4070 // implemented
4071 friend class WasmModuleObjectBuilder;
4072
4073 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Deserialize(
4074 Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4075 const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4076 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Compile(Isolate* isolate,
4077 const uint8_t* start,
4078 size_t length);
4079 static CallerOwnedBuffer AsCallerOwned(
4080 const TransferrableModule::OwnedBuffer& buff) {
4081 return {buff.first.get(), buff.second};
4082 }
4083
4084 WasmCompiledModule();
4085 static void CheckCast(Value* obj);
4086};

4089 public:
4090 WasmModuleObjectBuilder(Isolate* isolate) : isolate_(isolate) {}
4091 // The buffer passed into OnBytesReceived is owned by the caller.
4092 void OnBytesReceived(const uint8_t*, size_t size);
4093 MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Finish();
4094
4095 private:

4097 // TODO(ahaas): We probably need none of this below here once streamed

6281struct JitCodeEvent {
6282 enum EventType {
6283 CODE_ADDED,
6284 CODE_MOVED,
6285 CODE_REMOVED,
6286 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6287 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6288 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6289 };
6290 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6291 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6292 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6293 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6294 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6295 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6296
6297 // Type of event.
6298 EventType type;
6299 // Start of the instructions.
6300 void* code_start;
6301 // Size of the instructions.
6302 size_t code_len;
6303 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6304 Local<UnboundScript> script;
6305 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6306 // code line information which is returned from the
6307 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6308 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6309 void* user_data;
6310
6311 struct name_t {
6312 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6313 // zero-terminated.
6314 const char* str;
6315 // Number of chars in str.
6316 size_t len;
6317 };
6318
6319 struct line_info_t {
6320 // PC offset
6321 size_t offset;
6322 // Code postion
6323 size_t pos;
6324 // The position type.
6325 PositionType position_type;
6326 };
6327
6328 union {
6329 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6330 struct name_t name;
6331
6332 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6333 struct line_info_t line_info;
6334
6335 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6336 void* new_code_start;
6337 };
6338};
6339
6345enum RAILMode {
6346 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6347 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6348 // Throughput may be throttled.
6349 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6350 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6351 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6352 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
6353 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
6354 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
6355 // in this mode.
6356 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
6357 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
6358 // turn off latency optimizations.
6359 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
6360};
6361

6366 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
6367 // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
6368 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
6369};

7986template <class T>
7987class Maybe {
7988 public:
7989 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
7990 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
7991
7995 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
7996
8001 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8002 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8003 return IsJust();
8004 }
8005
8010 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8011 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8012 return value_;
8013 }
8014
8019 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8020 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8021 }
8022
8023 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8024 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8025 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8026 }
8027
8028 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8029 return !operator==(other);
8030 }
8031
8032 private:
8033 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8034 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8035
8036 bool has_value_;
8037 T value_;
8038
8039 template <class U>
8040 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8041 template <class U>
8042 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8043};
8044
8045
8046template <class T>
8047inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
8048 return Maybe<T>();
8049}
8050
8051
8052template <class T>
8053inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
8054 return Maybe<T>(t);
8055}

8588namespace internal {
8589
8590const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
8591const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
8592const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
8593
8594// Tag information for HeapObject.
8595const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
8596const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
8597const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
8598
8599// Tag information for Smi.
8600const int kSmiTag = 0;
8601const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
8602const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
8603
8604template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
8605
8606template<int kSmiShiftSize>
8607V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8608 int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8609 uintptr_t tagged_value =
8610 (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
8611 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
8612}
8613
8614// Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
8615template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
8616 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
8617 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8618 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8619 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8620 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8621 // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
8622 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
8623 }
8624 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8625 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8626 }
8627 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8628 // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
8629 // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
8630 // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
8631 // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
8632 //
8633 // CAUTION: The original code below:
8634 // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
8635 // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
8636 // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
8637 // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
8638 // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
8639 return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
8640 }
8641};
8642
8643// Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
8644template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
8645 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
8646 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8647 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8648 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8649 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8650 // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
8651 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
8652 }
8653 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8654 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8655 }
8656 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8657 // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
8658 return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
8659 }
8660};
8661
8662typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
8663const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
8664const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
8665V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
8666V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }
8667
8673class Internals {
8674 public:
8675 // These values match non-compiler-dependent values defined within
8676 // the implementation of v8.
8677 static const int kHeapObjectMapOffset = 0;
8678 static const int kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset =
8679 1 * kApiPointerSize + kApiIntSize;
8680 static const int kStringResourceOffset = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
8681
8682 static const int kOddballKindOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize + sizeof(double);
8683 static const int kForeignAddressOffset = kApiPointerSize;
8684 static const int kJSObjectHeaderSize = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
8685 static const int kFixedArrayHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
8686 static const int kContextHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
8687 static const int kContextEmbedderDataIndex = 5;
8688 static const int kFullStringRepresentationMask = 0x0f;
8689 static const int kStringEncodingMask = 0x8;
8690 static const int kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag = 0x02;
8691 static const int kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag = 0x0a;
8692
8693 static const int kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset = 0 * kApiPointerSize;
8694 static const int kExternalMemoryOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize;
8695 static const int kExternalMemoryLimitOffset =
8696 kExternalMemoryOffset + kApiInt64Size;
8697 static const int kIsolateRootsOffset = kExternalMemoryLimitOffset +
8698 kApiInt64Size + kApiInt64Size +
8699 kApiPointerSize + kApiPointerSize;
8700 static const int kUndefinedValueRootIndex = 4;
8701 static const int kTheHoleValueRootIndex = 5;
8702 static const int kNullValueRootIndex = 6;
8703 static const int kTrueValueRootIndex = 7;
8704 static const int kFalseValueRootIndex = 8;
8705 static const int kEmptyStringRootIndex = 9;
8706
8707 static const int kNodeClassIdOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize;
8708 static const int kNodeFlagsOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize + 3;
8709 static const int kNodeStateMask = 0x7;
8710 static const int kNodeStateIsWeakValue = 2;
8711 static const int kNodeStateIsPendingValue = 3;
8712 static const int kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue = 4;
8713 static const int kNodeIsIndependentShift = 3;
8714 static const int kNodeIsActiveShift = 4;
8715
8716 static const int kJSApiObjectType = 0xbb;
8717 static const int kJSObjectType = 0xbc;
8718 static const int kFirstNonstringType = 0x80;
8719 static const int kOddballType = 0x82;
8720 static const int kForeignType = 0x86;
8721
8722 static const int kUndefinedOddballKind = 5;
8723 static const int kNullOddballKind = 3;
8724
8725 static const uint32_t kNumIsolateDataSlots = 4;
8726
8727 V8_EXPORT static void CheckInitializedImpl(v8::Isolate* isolate);
8728 V8_INLINE static void CheckInitialized(v8::Isolate* isolate) {
8729#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8730 CheckInitializedImpl(isolate);
8731#endif
8732 }
8733
8734 V8_INLINE static bool HasHeapObjectTag(const internal::Object* value) {
8735 return ((reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) & kHeapObjectTagMask) ==
8736 kHeapObjectTag);
8737 }
8738
8739 V8_INLINE static int SmiValue(const internal::Object* value) {
8740 return PlatformSmiTagging::SmiToInt(value);
8741 }
8742
8743 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8744 return PlatformSmiTagging::IntToSmi(value);
8745 }
8746
8747 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8748 return PlatformSmiTagging::IsValidSmi(value);
8749 }
8750
8751 V8_INLINE static int GetInstanceType(const internal::Object* obj) {
8752 typedef internal::Object O;
8753 O* map = ReadField<O*>(obj, kHeapObjectMapOffset);
8754 // Map::InstanceType is defined so that it will always be loaded into
8755 // the LS 8 bits of one 16-bit word, regardless of endianess.
8756 return ReadField<uint16_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset) & 0xff;
8757 }
8758
8759 V8_INLINE static int GetOddballKind(const internal::Object* obj) {
8760 typedef internal::Object O;
8761 return SmiValue(ReadField<O*>(obj, kOddballKindOffset));
8762 }
8763
8764 V8_INLINE static bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {
8765 int representation = (instance_type & kFullStringRepresentationMask);
8766 return representation == kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag;
8767 }
8768
8769 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
8770 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8771 return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
8772 }
8773
8774 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
8775 bool value, int shift) {
8776 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8777 uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
8778 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
8779 }
8780
8781 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {
8782 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8783 return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
8784 }
8785
8786 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
8787 uint8_t value) {
8788 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8789 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
8790 }
8791
8792 V8_INLINE static void SetEmbedderData(v8::Isolate* isolate,
8793 uint32_t slot,
8794 void* data) {
8795 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) +
8796 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
8797 *reinterpret_cast<void**>(addr) = data;
8798 }
8799
8800 V8_INLINE static void* GetEmbedderData(const v8::Isolate* isolate,
8801 uint32_t slot) {
8802 const uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(isolate) +
8803 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
8804 return *reinterpret_cast<void* const*>(addr);
8805 }
8806
8807 V8_INLINE static internal::Object** GetRoot(v8::Isolate* isolate,
8808 int index) {
8809 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) + kIsolateRootsOffset;
8810 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(addr + index * kApiPointerSize);
8811 }
8812
8813 template <typename T>
8814 V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
8815 const uint8_t* addr =
8816 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
8817 return *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(addr);
8818 }
8819
8820 template <typename T>
8821 V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
8822 typedef internal::Object O;
8823 typedef internal::Internals I;
8824 O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
8825 int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
8826 (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
8827 O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
8828 int value_offset =
8829 I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8830 return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
8831 }
8832};

8851 T* that_ptr = that;

8897 V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
8898 p));
8899}

8901
8902template <class T, class M>
8903template <class S, class M2>
8904void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
8905 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
8906 this->Reset();
8907 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
8908 internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
8909 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
8910 M::Copy(that, this);
8911}
8912
8913
8914template <class T>
8915bool PersistentBase<T>::IsIndependent() const {
8916 typedef internal::Internals I;
8917 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
8918 return I::GetNodeFlag(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_),
8919 I::kNodeIsIndependentShift);
8920}
8921
8922
8923template <class T>
8924bool PersistentBase<T>::IsNearDeath() const {
8925 typedef internal::Internals I;
8926 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
8927 uint8_t node_state =
8928 I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
8929 return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
8930 node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
8931}
8932
8933
8934template <class T>
8935bool PersistentBase<T>::IsWeak() const {
8936 typedef internal::Internals I;
8937 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
8938 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_)) ==
8939 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
8940}

8943template <class T>
8944void PersistentBase<T>::Reset() {
8945 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
8946 V8::DisposeGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
8947 val_ = 0;
8948}

8954 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
8955 Reset();
8956 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
8957 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);
8958}

8965 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
8966 Reset();
8967 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
8968 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);
8969}

9020template <class T>
9021void PersistentBase<T>::SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id) {
9022 typedef internal::Internals I;
9023 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
9024 internal::Object** obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
9025 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
9026 *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr) = class_id;
9027}

9032 typedef internal::Internals I;
9033 if (this->IsEmpty()) return 0;
9034 internal::Object** obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
9035 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
9036 return *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr);
9037}

9076template<typename T>
9077void ReturnValue<T>::Set(double i) {
9078 TYPE_CHECK(T, Number);
9079 Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9080}
9081
9082template<typename T>
9083void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
9084 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9085 typedef internal::Internals I;
9086 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
9087 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
9088 return;
9089 }
9090 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9091}
9092
9093template<typename T>
9094void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
9095 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9096 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
9097 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
9098 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
9099 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
9100 return;
9101 }
9102 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
9103}
9104
9105template<typename T>
9106void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
9107 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
9108 typedef internal::Internals I;
9109 int root_index;
9110 if (value) {
9111 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
9112 } else {
9113 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
9114 }
9115 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
9116}
9117
9118template<typename T>
9119void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
9120 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
9121 typedef internal::Internals I;
9122 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
9123}

9125template<typename T>
9126void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
9127 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
9128 typedef internal::Internals I;
9129 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
9130}

9136 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
9137}

9139template <typename T>
9140Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
9141 // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
9142 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
9143}
9144
9145template <typename T>
9146Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
9147 typedef internal::Internals I;
9148 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
9149 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
9150 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
9151}

9156 // Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
9157 TYPE_CHECK(S*, Primitive);
9158}

9160template<typename T>

9162 // Default value is always the pointer below value_ on the stack.
9163 return value_[-1];
9164}

9311
9312Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
9313#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9314 typedef internal::Object O;
9315 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9316 typedef internal::Internals I;
9317 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9318 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9319 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9320 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9321 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9322 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
9323 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9324 O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
9325 O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
9326 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9327 }
9328#endif
9329 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
9330}
9331
9332
9333void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
9334#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9335 typedef internal::Object O;
9336 typedef internal::Internals I;
9337 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9338 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9339 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9340 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9341 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9342 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
9343 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9344 return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
9345 }
9346#endif
9347 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
9348}

9366
9367String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
9368 typedef internal::Object O;
9369 typedef internal::Internals I;
9370 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9371 String::ExternalStringResource* result;
9372 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
9373 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9374 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
9375 } else {
9376 result = NULL;
9377 }
9378#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9379 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
9380#endif
9381 return result;
9382}
9383
9384
9385String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
9386 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
9387 typedef internal::Object O;
9388 typedef internal::Internals I;
9389 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9390 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
9391 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
9392 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
9393 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
9394 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
9395 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9396 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
9397 }
9398#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9399 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
9400#endif
9401 return resource;
9402}

9412
9413bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
9414 typedef internal::Object O;
9415 typedef internal::Internals I;
9416 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9417 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9418 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9419 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
9420}

9426#else

9431bool Value::QuickIsNull() const {
9432 typedef internal::Object O;
9433 typedef internal::Internals I;
9434 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9435 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9436 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9437 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kNullOddballKind);
9438}

9440bool Value::IsNullOrUndefined() const {
9441#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9442 return FullIsNull() || FullIsUndefined();
9443#else
9444 return QuickIsNullOrUndefined();
9445#endif
9446}
9447
9448bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
9449 typedef internal::Object O;
9450 typedef internal::Internals I;
9451 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9452 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9453 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9454 int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
9455 return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
9456}

9470 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9471 return (I::GetInstanceType(obj) < I::kFirstNonstringType);
9472}

9911
9912int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
9913 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
9914 typedef internal::Internals I;
9915 int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
9916 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
9917 const int64_t external_memory_limit = *reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
9918 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
9919 const int64_t amount = *external_memory + change_in_bytes;
9920 *external_memory = amount;
9921 if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > external_memory_limit) {
9922 ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
9923 }
9924 return *external_memory;
9925}
9926
9927Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
9928#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9929 typedef internal::Object O;
9930 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9931 typedef internal::Internals I;
9932 HO* context = *reinterpret_cast<HO**>(this);
9933 O** result =
9934 HandleScope::CreateHandle(context, I::ReadEmbedderData<O*>(this, index));
9935 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9936#else
9937 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
9938#endif
9939}

9946#else
9947 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);

9949}
